SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 648
By Yager
A RESOLUTION to designate the State of Tennessee a Purple
Heart State.
WHEREAS, the State of Tennessee and its citizens have great admiration and gratitude
for all the men and women who have served, and are serving, in the United States Armed
Forces; and
WHEREAS, veterans have paid the high price of freedom by leaving behind their
families and communities and placing themselves in harm's way for the good of all; and
WHEREAS, the sacrifices and hardship that war causes will never be forgotten; and
WHEREAS, members of the United States Armed Forces have been awarded the
Purple Heart in recognition of injuries, and sometimes death, sustained in fighting an enemy
force; and
WHEREAS, the State of Tennessee honors the service and sacrifice of our nation's men
and women in uniform and seeks to remember and recognize those veterans who are recipients
of the Purple Heart; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby designate the State of Tennessee as a
Purple Heart State in recognition of our military veterans and the many Purple Heart recipients
who have called the Volunteer State home.
